<L>__{interior exterior bus. day}
<A>__{the doors open and terry comes up the steps and into the bus. outside, sammy watches him pay the driver and move through the bus toward his seat. the bus doors close.}
<L>__{exterior bus. continuous}
<A>__{sammy waves till the bus drives all the way down main street, turns a corner and is gone.}
<L>__{interior bus. continuous}
<A>__{terry, in his seat, turns forward and watches the view go by. he smiles a little.}
<L>__{interior sammy's car (moving). day}
<A>__{the morning sunlight flickers through the windshield into the car as sammy drives along toward work. she passes the town hall clock and sees that it's 9:20. she dries her damp cheek with a forearm and rolls down her window to let the morning breeze blow through. squaring her shoulders a little, she drives through town at a slow and easy pace.}
<C>__{the end}
